b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Topaz Video AI is best suited for video upscaling professionals, restoring old footage, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Veed.io, meanwhile, shines for quick online video editing, subtitle creation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2019, Topaz Video AI describes itself as \"AI-powered video upscaling and enhancement.\" Veed.io, established in 2018, positions itself as \"Online video editor with powerful AI tools.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Topaz Video AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0). However, this does not mean Veed.io is a poor choice — far from it. Veed.io excels in its own right, particularly for quick online video editing and subtitle creation.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value best-in-class upscaling quality, go with Topaz Video AI. If excellent auto-subtitles matters more to you, Veed.io is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
